ratings.comment: This is the hardest CSD class I have taken so far in the major. Would not recommend if you have a full schedule with other challenging classes. It is blended, but the "in class learning activities" are not posted on canvas even though they are supposedly not mandatory. Rountrey makes things much harder than they need to be

Carrie is a good person and knows what she's talking about. However, we were assigned online lectures to watch, making meeting for class pointless. The tests are alright, and one of the 3 midterms is dropped. I had to spend lots of time studying for this class on my own. Have to willing to put in work.

For a tougher CSD class, Carrie makes it easy to get an A. She posts learning objectives which are basically the test questions, and the practice quizzes are almost always test questions as well. Attendance is mandatory but lectures are online which made it sort of pointless. :/ However, Carrie is super nice and made it interesting! Recommend!!
Rountrey is an amazing professor for some tougher introductory material in biology. She is there for you all the time and offers a friendly atmosphere when in her class.
